This paper deals with the formalization and verification of a parser interpreter for Parsing Expression Grammars (PEGs), which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The use of a rich type system for formalization and verification suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper's focus on ensuring soundness and completeness of parsing suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
